<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Imagine I create a feed (RSS) with Zend_Builder from an array, I don't have to set 'lastUpdate' date as it isn't mandatory.
Now if I set a 'lastUpdate' on each entry the main pubDate (=lastUpdate) must be the max timestamp of those used
in the entries.
But by default the Zend_Feed_Builder_Header set the LastUpdate as now()...</p>

<p>Wouldn't be smarter, if not specified it take the max timestamp of the entries ?</p>

